LeddarTech, a Canadian software company specializing in automotive solutions, has announced that it will no longer participate in the Consumer Electronics Show (CES) 2025 and has taken key strategic steps. The company presented the LeddarVision Surround (LVS-2+), a cutting-edge peripheral software solution designed for level 2/2+ urban and highway driving assistance applications. This technology utilizes the TDA4VH-Q1 processor from Texas Instruments (TI) and has enabled LeddarTech to receive the second advance royalty payment of $3 million under its licensing agreement.

LeddarTech also organized demonstrations of its software platform in a kiosk and held high-level meetings with equipment suppliers, Tier 1 providers, and strategic partners. The company identified potential clients and laid the groundwork for numerous new partnerships with major players in the automotive industry.

The event's closure confirms that the company is ready to provide exceptional value to its clients. LeddarTech has also announced that 2025 marks a new and exciting chapter for the company, with strategic partnerships, growing client interest, new products, and an overwhelmingly positive market reaction to CES.

LeddarTech is a global software company founded in 2007, based in Quebec, and with additional R&D centers in Montreal and Tel Aviv (Israel). The company develops and offers comprehensive low-level sensor fusion and perception software solutions based on artificial intelligence, enabling the deployment of ADAS, AD, and parking applications.

LeddarTech's shares are listed on the NASDAQ under the symbol "LDTC". The company has filed over 170 patent applications (87 granted) that enhance the capabilities of driving assistance, autonomous driving, and parking systems.

